                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.51/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Governor of the Federal Reserve Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to enclose copy of a
                    letter from Mr. James B. Forgan, President of the First National Bank of
                    Chicago, to Hon. F. A. Delano, Vice Governor of the Federal Reserve Board.<note
                        n="11" xml:id="d144fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> As the matter referred to is one of
                    Governmental policy, I beg to ask you to read it, sending me any reply you may
                    care to make, which I will forward to Mr. Forgan.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. S. Hamlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
